               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate when="1913">
                        According to <ref target="#coloph1"/>, the manuscript was written in the year of mercy 
                        <date calendar="ethiopian" when-custom="1905" when="1913">1905 EC</date>, in the month of <foreign xml:lang="gez">Ḫǝdār</foreign>.
                        The text also mentions the names of King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName>, Metropolitan <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6876Matewos">Mātewos X</persName>, and 
                        Patriarch <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3259CyrilV">Cyril V</persName>.
                     </origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>According to the account on the manuscripts’ provenance given by Tisserant, this manuscript is among those
                     acquired by <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4805Grebaut">Sylvain Grébaut</persName> in <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1216AddisA">ʾAddis ʾAbabā</placeName> 
                     in <date when="1925"/> with funds of
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14055SaintJ">Jean Saint</persName>. 
                     The manuscripts originated from Šawā (ʾAddis ʾAbabā, Dabra Libānos, Dabra Bǝrhān),
                     Goǧǧām (Dimā Giyorgis, Marṭula Māryām, Dabra Warq) and Bagemdǝr (Gondar, ʾAzazo Takla Hāymānot), and very few from Tǝgrāy.
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition when="1928">The manuscript entered the library on <date>18 April 1928</date>.</acquisition>
               </history>
          
